Create Date table and create relationship with the main table 9

Step 1. Create date table


Steps
  1. Click on the Data Tab as shown in the steps above.
  2. Click on New Table button
  3. Enter the following formula in to the Formula Bar and press Enter

                    Calendar = CALENDARAUTO(12)


Step 2. Change  the Date column format


Steps
  1. Click on the Date column in the Calendar Table
  2. Click on the format tab to show the drop down list
  3. Select The Date Month Year format


Step 3. Add columns to the newly created Calendar Table


Steps
  1. Click on New Column button 
  2. Enter  Year = YEAR('Calendar'[Date]) into the Formula Bar and click Enter
  3. Follow the same step to create  additional columns by entering the following formula

                 Month = MONTH('Calendar'[Date])

MonthName = FORMAT('Calendar'[Date], "MMMM")

Days of The Week = FORMAT('Calendar'[Date], "DDDD")

WeekNum = WEEKNUM('Calendar'[Date],2)

Date Number = WEEKDAY('Calendar'[Date], 2)

After creating the new columns the Calendar table looks like the following.



Step 4. Mark Calendar Table as a date table

Steps
  1. Click on the Calendar table
  2. Click on Mark as date Table button
  3. Select Date from Mark as Date Table dialogue box and click Ok.


Step 5. Create relationship between Calendar and Mass Shooting tables


Steps

  1. Select the MonthName column
  2. Click on Sort by Column button
  3. Select the Month column from the drop down list.


Step 6. Create relationship between Calendar and Mass Shooting tables

To create relationship between the Calendar table and Mass Shooting table drag and drop the Date column from the Calendar table to the Mass Shooting. This will create a One to Many relationship between the two tables as shown below.


This is a good video on how to create Date Table.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gyvhM5eiT0U
